{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"ffaa83f0-0beb-4074-bd00-3df769c59e91","content":"No files found in the working directory. Since you described the page but didn't provide it, here's exactly how to convert it:\n\n### 1. Add `x:DataType` to your XAML\n\nIn `SettingsPage.xaml`, add the `x:DataType` attribute to the root `ContentPage` element, pointing to your ViewModel type:\n\n```xml\n<ContentPage xmlns=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui\"\n             xmlns:x=\"http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml\"\n             xmlns:vm=\"clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels\"\n             x:Class=\"YourApp.Views.SettingsPage\"\n             x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\">\n\n    <VerticalStackLayout Padding=\"20\" Spacing=\"15\">\n\n        <Label Text=\"{Binding Theme}\" />\n\n        <Switch IsToggled=\"{Binding NotificationsEnabled}\" />\n\n        <Label Text=\"{Binding FontSize, StringFormat='Font size: {0}'}\" />\n\n    </VerticalStackLayout>\n</ContentPage>\n```\n\n**Key change:** `x:DataType=\"vm:SettingsViewModel\"` tells the XAML compiler the type of `BindingContext`, so every `{Binding ...}` is verified at compile time.\n\n### 2. Catch binding errors at build time\n\nAdd this to your `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n    <!-- Treat XAML binding warnings as errors -->\n    <WarningsAsErrors>$(WarningsAsErrors);XC0045</WarningsAsErrors>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n`XC0045` is the diagnostic for compiled-binding mismatches. With this, a typo like `{Binding Themee}` becomes a **build error** instead of a silent runtime failure.\n\n### 3. Important caveats\n\n- **`x:DataType` is inherited** — child elements use the same type unless overridden.\n- **To opt out** for a specific binding (e.g., binding to the page itself), use `x:DataType=\"\"` on that element to disable compiled bindings locally.\n- **DataTemplates** need their own `x:DataType` matching the item type, not the parent ViewModel.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"9430c821-9dec-498c-9e20-49101e8ccdcf","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The files don't exist yet. The user is asking me to convert their page, but they haven't provided the files. Let me check if there are any files at all in the working directory.","outputTokens":594,"requestId":"77C9:204131:85A9A47:93D444A:69EABDC2"},"id":"82c68033-d17a-4803-80f6-dd9668d0874a","timestamp":"2026-04-24T00:48:15.231Z","parentId":"6b846464-0f50-41a5-bf9b-3ace5d324b20"}
